subSubSection.paragraph:
Capsicum annuum var. glabriusculum
is the most widely distributed member of the genus, from southern United States of America to northern Bolivia and northern Brazil (Fig. 
24
). It is more common in Mexico, Central America, the Caribbean, Colombia and Venezuela. In eastern Australia, it is reported as a weed (
Symon 1981
; 
Purdie et al. 1982
).

